            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I took a look at the issue, these are my observations:\n\nIt seems that `stterm` has issues with escape sequences alternating the cursor. (Not the text, but specifically the cursor.)\n\n`stterm` v0.8.4-1:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d03387a3-80b3-4b06-81a5-021e3d1f6292)\n\nThe second command, instead of changing the cursor, was triggering the following error:\n```\nerresc: unknown str ESC]12\n```\n`stterm` v0.9.2:\n\nNow indeed, as @uio23 added, the following issue has been fixed in later versions:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c6bf5063-fa17-4d51-994d-49f2721e7ad6)\n\n... however, still, the 2nd command (i.e. restoring cursor color) is triggering the following error:\n```\nerresc: unknown str ESC]112ESC\\\n```\nvery similar to the observations by @uio23 in \"What I tried\"/Method A/Outcome. \n\nOverall meaning that even if we can easily adjust Neovim code to set the cursor color... We can't reset it after 😅 \n(Meaning that perhaps not setting it at all is still the best solution here...? -- Not until `stterm` is ready for it, the least.)\n",
