        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "## Compatible\n_For Cs:_ `printf “\\033]12;red\\007”` works, changing text and cursor color to red\n\n## Incompatible\n _For Cr:_ `printf “\\033]112\\007` doesn’t reset the cursor color.\nHowever, sending this unknown termcode doesn’t produce any response or unexpected behaviour.\n\n## What I’ve done \n* Emailed [bug-ncurses@gnu.org](mailto:bug-ncurses@gnu.org), CC’ing [dickey@invisible-island.net](mailto:dickey@invisible-island.net) asking to add \n`Cs=\\E]12;%p1%s\\007 ` entry to the ncurses definitions.\n* In the meantime, built NeoVim from the master branch, `v0.11.0-dev-1667+g096ae3bfd7-dirty`, editing the `augment_terminfo()` to include ST as a seperate `||` for this branch to run.\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/096ae3bfd7075dce69c70182ccedcd6d33e66d31/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L2381-L2386\nNeoVim’s behaviour now matches the expected behaviour.\n## Closing\nI’ll update with a response from ncurses maintainers, and if they refuse to add the Cs entry for ST, I’ll be glad to make a pull request with this fix (if that’s desirable?).\n",
